<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1909-11-12T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1909-11-12T00:00:00-05:00" n="418" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d418">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 6369/268.</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                Minister <persName type="to">Merry</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram—Paraphrase.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1909-11-12"><hi rend="italic">November 12,
                                    1909</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>Mr. Knox informs Mr. Merry that the department hopes that Costa Rica will
                            continue to take every means at her disposal to compel the faithful
                            observance of the treaties of Washington.</p>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>